==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sharp-cut
<hw>Sharp-cut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Cut sharply or
definitely, or so as to make a clear, well-defined impression, as the
lines of an engraved plate, and the like; clear-cut; hence, having great
distinctness; well-defined; clear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sharpen</ent>⟦br⟧
